  "body": "Hello,\r\n\r\nWe are trying to implement the voluntary exit command before the ETH2.0 merge, and I had a general question on epoch, and how it works.\r\n\r\n- I understand the formula to calculate the epoch is given here: https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/blob/d4f3257f609b7a6690b8fcf0845457602fe0eb84/validator/client/propose.go#L216\r\n- I want to understand how epoch works while broadcasting a voluntary exit message. For example if we broadcast a message at an earlier epoch (so the epoch is already proposed), does that just invalidate the broadcast? \r\n- Is there a better technique of calculating the epoch? Potentially looking at the `target` `attestations` of the last proposed slot and appending by +1?",
