    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "You can sign the voluntary exit with any epoch you want. The only caveat is that you also need to sign it with a fork version (corresponding to the epoch you signed it for) and the exit will be valid for the current fork and the next fork version. \r\n\r\nThis allows you to sign an exit in the future, that will only be valid when the epoch that you signed it for is already reached. Notice though that you cannot sign for a fork that you don't already know will happen. \r\n\r\nPlease close this issue if this reply did solve your question, and if it didn't please close it anyway and reach us in Discord that will be more appropriate than on this setup. ",
